  "prompt": "How do I send gif in whatsapp?",
  "response": "To send a GIF in WhatsApp, follow these steps:\n\nOn iPhone:\n1. Open WhatsApp\n2. Select a chat\n3. Tap the text input field\n4. Tap the GIF/sticker icon (usually next to the text field)\n5. Browse or search for a GIF\n6. Tap the GIF to send\n\nOn Android:\n1. Open WhatsApp\n2. Select a chat\n3. Tap the text input field\n4. Tap the emoji icon\n5. Tap the GIF icon (usually looks like a play button)\n6. Search or browse GIFs\n7. Tap the GIF to send\n\nAlternative method:\n1. You can also save a GIF to your phone\n2. Open the chat\n3. Tap the attachment icon\n4. Choose Gallery/Photos\n5. Select the GIF file\n6. Send\n\nVia GIPHY or other GIF websites:\n1. Find a GIF online\n2. Download or copy it\n3. Send through WhatsApp using the methods above\n\nNote: The exact steps might vary slightly depending on your phone model and WhatsApp version.",
